{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"7833c8eb-7119-4595-b5bd-0b0e41f897f5","content":"Yes, both are known MSTest v4 breaking changes. Here's what's happening:\n\n## 1. Tests lost history in Azure DevOps\n\nMSTest v4 changed the **default fully-qualified test ID** format. Azure DevOps matches test history by ID, so all tests appear \"new.\" You can restore the old IDs by adding to your `.runsettings`:\n\n```xml\n<MSTest>\n  <TestIdGenerationStrategy>Legacy</TestIdGenerationStrategy>\n</MSTest>\n```\n\nOr accept the new IDs and let history rebuild going forward.\n\n## 2. `TestContext.TestName` in `[ClassInitialize]`\n\nIn v4, the `TestContext` passed to `[ClassInitialize]` is a **class-level context** — it no longer carries an individual test name. Accessing `TestContext.TestName` (line 13 in your code) now throws `InvalidOperationException`.\n\n**Fix:** Remove that access, or gate it:\n\n```csharp\n[ClassInitialize]\npublic static void ClassInit(TestContext context)\n{\n    // context.TestName is unavailable here in v4\n    // Use context.FullyQualifiedTestClassName instead, or\n    // move per-test logic to [TestInitialize]\n}\n```\n\n## 3. Other v4 changes to watch for\n\n| Area | Change |\n|------|--------|\n| **Parallelism** | Tests run in parallel by default. Add `[assembly: Parallelize(Scope = ExecutionScope.ClassLevel)]` or disable if you have shared state. |\n| **Timeout behavior** | `[Timeout]` now uses `CancellationToken` (cooperative cancellation) instead of `Thread.Abort`. Long-running code must check the token. |\n| **Assert.ThrowsException** | Now validates the *exact* exception type; previously matched derived types. Use `Assert.ThrowsExactly` or switch to `Assert.Throws<T>` for inheritance-inclusive matching. |\n| **DataRow display names** | Parameterized tests may produce different display names, also affecting CI history. |\n| **Removed APIs** | `DeploymentItem` and some legacy attributes were removed. |\n\nThe biggest silent issue is usually **parallel execution** — tests that passed sequentially may now have race conditions.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"6e0aeda0-54c8-4672-a153-2c5e8d4d9433","outputTokens":543,"requestId":"E3C5:AB6AD:241AA73:28081F7:6A053EB5"},"id":"a377b0cc-3616-40d2-b14f-37148465a852","timestamp":"2026-05-14T03:17:23.171Z","parentId":"7899352e-ab2d-4428-8285-55c176d28902"}
